\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 17.        Bulbocodium}      L.
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By D.H. Valentine. 
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Perennials with a corm. Leaves linear to lanceolate. Perianth petaloid, deeply 6-partite, free from the base but with long, narrow claws forming a tube below, and joined by teeth or auricles at the base of the limb. Stamens inserted at the base of the limb; filaments slender; anthers versatile. Ovary 3-locular, sessile; ovules many. Style undivided at base, 3-fid at apex. Capsule oblong, 3-valved, opening only at the apex. Seeds globose.
