\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. B. vernum} L., {\i Sp. Pl. }294 (1753). Corm up to 3 cm in diameter. Plant 5-20 cm. Leaves 3-4, up to 15 × 1·5 cm, with sheathing base and patent limb, linear to linear-lanceolate, obtuse, appearing in spring at the same time as the flowers. Flowers 1(-3), 4-8·5 cm, pink, rarely white. Perianth-segments linear-lanceolate, acute, each with a pair of acute teeth at base of limb. Capsule 1·5-2 cm. {\i Mountain meadows. Pyrenees, S.W. & W.C. Alps; one station in S. Austria.} Au Ga He Hs It.
\par

