\pard\f0\fs28 Perennial herbs. Corm with thick, black membranous tunic. Leaves all basal. Lower part of leaves and flowers covered by a membranous cylindrical sheath. Flowers solitary or in fascicles, terminal, subsessile, pinkish-purple. Perianth-segments free, with a long, narrow claw and shorter, wider, narrowly elliptical to narrowly obovate limb. Stamens inserted at the base of the limb. Styles free. Capsule oblong, septicidal with 3 apiculate valves.
