\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. M. attica} (Spruner ex Tommasini) Boiss. & Spruner in Boiss.,{\i  Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.}{\b  1}({\b 5}): 67 (1844) ({\i M. rhodopaea} Velen.). Corm 15-20(-30) × 10-15(-25) mm, without stolons. Leaves up to 17 cm × 3-5(-8) mm, appearing with the flowers; margin scabrid. Flowers (1-)2-3(-5). Limb of perianth-segments (12-)15-25(-45) × 2-4 mm, obtuse, expanded at base. Anthers 1·5-3 mm, ¼-½ as long as filaments, violet, dorsifixed, versatile. Capsule 12-20 mm, oblong, shortly pedicellate, with styles and claws of perianth-segments long-persistent. Seeds 2-2·2 × 1·6-1·8 mm, oblong, with a more or less triangular beak. Autumn flowering. {\i Dry places. S. Bulgaria, S. Greece.} Bu Gr.
