\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. M. sobolifera} C. A. Meyer in Fischer & C. A. Meyer,{\i  Ind. Sem. Hort. Petrop.}{\b  1}: 34 (1835). Corm 7-15 × 5-10 mm, with underground stolons. Leaves up to 15 cm × 3-6(-8) mm, appearing with the flowers, sulcate; margin smooth. Flowers 1-2. Limb of perianth-segments 20-40 × 2·5-5(-8) mm, obtuse, the base sagittate with 2 descending linear appendages. Anthers 1·5-3·5 mm, 1/3-1/2 as long as filaments, violet, dorsifixed, versatile. Capsule 15-20 mm, oblong. Seeds subglobose. Spring-flowering. 2n = 54.{\i  E. & C. parts of Balkan peninsula; E. Romania}. Bu ?Gr Ju Rm Tu.
