\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. M. pyrenaica} (Pourret) P. Fourn.,{\i  Quatre Fl. Fr.} 157 (1935) ({\i M. montana} Lange,{\i  M. bulbocodium} Ramond). Corm 20-25(-30) × 15-20(-30) mm. Leaves up to 22 cm × (3·5-)4-8 (-10) mm, usually appearing after the flowers, plicate. Flowers solitary, rarely 2. Limb of perianth-segments (25-)30-45(-65) × (3-)4-6·5(-11) mm, obtuse, rarely emarginate. Anthers (5·5-)8-12(-17) mm, longer than filaments, yellow, basifixed. Capsule (10-)15-20(-25) mm, oblong. Seeds c. 2 × 1·5 mm, globose-pyriform, apiculate. Autumn-flowering. 2n = 60, 54+0-6B.{\i  Dry places. • Iberian peninsula, C. Pyrenees.} Ga Hs Lu.
